title: Warrior
content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:WarriorThe RuneScape Classic Wiki also has an article on: classicrsw:Warrior

Warrior could refer to:

  • Warrior (Rellekka), a level 48 human (attackable) found in Rellekka
  • Warrior (Lost City), a non-player character from the Lost City quest
  • Warrior (music track), a music track from The Fremennik Trials quest
  • Al-Kharid warrior, a thievable and attackable level 9 human found in Al Kharid
  • Warrior woman, a thievable level 24 human found in various places
  • Combat classes include melee fighters, sometimes called "warriors"
  • Warriors' Guild, a guild in Burthorpe it is open to players with a Strength and Attack level of a combined 130+ or 99 in one of the skills
    • Warrior Guild Potion Shop, a shop that sells normal attack, strength and defence potions in the Warriors' Guild
    • Warrior Guild Armoury, a shop that sells various melee equipment from bronze to mithril in the Warriors' Guild.
    • Warrior Guild Food Shop, a shop that sells a variety of food in the Warriors' Guild.
    • Warrior guild token, a currency usable within the Warriors' Guild to enter the cyclops chamber.
  • Spiritual warrior, a slayer monster located in the God Wars Dungeon and Wilderness God Wars Dungeon
  • Warrior ring or Warrior ring (i), a fremennik ring obtainable as a drop from Dagannoth Rex
 This page is used to distinguish between articles with similar names.
If an internal link led you to this disambiguation page, you may wish to change the link to point directly to the intended article.
